#What are the two values of a boolean data type
boolean data type: true and false
a = true
type(a)
b = false
type(b)
#What are the three boolean operators? 
Three boolean operators: AND, OR, NOT or AND NOT
#Write out the truth tables of both boolean operators i.e every possible combination of boolean values and their result. 
condition 1 (e.g., X):false, false, true, true
condition 2 (e.g., Y):false, true, false, true
NOT X ( ~ X ):true, true, false, false
X AND Y ( X && Y ):false, false, false, true
#What are the six comparison operators.
equal to, not equal to, greater than, greater than or equal to, less than, and less than or equal to.
#What is the difference between the equal operator and the assignment operator
The “=” is an assignment operator is used to assign the value on the right to the variable on the left.
