#Why are functions advantages to have in your programs
The advantages of using functions are: Reducing duplication of code. Decomposing complex problems into simpler pieces. Improving clarity of the code
The code in a function is executed when it is called.
A function is created with the def keyword.The statements in the block of the function must be indented. The def keyword is followed by the function name with round brackets and a colon
#If a function does not have a return value, what is the return value when the function is called?   
It returns none
